cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning with uncertainty is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science, but the focus on logic-based methods and neural-symbolic computing suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The use of Logic Programming with Kleene semantics and Input/Output logic also suggests that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses discourse and normative contexts, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), respectively. Finally, the use of neural-symbolic computing suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant sub-category.
